California 0.4.0 - 23 March 2015
--------------------------------

  * Fix UI issue where date span of event could not be reduced (#744147)
  * Add ftp, ftps support for WebCal
  * Update translations


California 0.3.1 - 3 February 2015
----------------------------------

  * Honor event's timezone when editing RRULEs (#741624)
  * Prevent black background when using Unity (#742310)
  * Assorted bug fixes
  * Updated translations


California 0.3.0 - 8 December 2014
----------------------------------

  * New Agenda view shows events as chronological list
  * Set and honor default calendar
  * Export event as .ics file
  * Fix moving events between calendars
  * Show and edit event attendees and organizer
  * Send invites to attendees when editing event
  * Fix nasty "Invalid DTSTAMP" problem: Bug #733319
  * Various bug fixes
  * Updated translations


California 0.2.0 - 30 September 2014
------------------------------------

  * F1 Help (thanks to Jim Campbell)
  * Migrate to GTK+ 3.12
  * Quick Add improvements
  * Display recurring event information as plain language summary
  * Remove calendar from EDS
  * Various UI improvements
  * Updated translations


California 0.1.4 - 19 August 2014
---------------------------------

  * Rebuild .c files when configuration changes
  * Updated German translations


California 0.1.3 - 15 August 2014
---------------------------------

  * Generic CalDAV support
  * Numerous Quick Add parser improvements
  * Use system/locale's defined first day of week
  * Move events between calendars
  * Improved event viewing and editing
  * Various bug fixes and improvements
  * Updated translations

California 0.1.2 - 18 July 2014
-------------------------------

  * Create, remove, and update recurring events
  * Quick Add parsing improvements
  * Event description, location support
  * Zoom display
  * Various bug fixes
  * Updated translations


California 0.1.1 - 23 May 2014
------------------------------

  * Added week view.
  * Rename calendars in the calendar manager.


California 0.1.0 - 1 May 2014
-----------------------------

  * First unstable release.
  * Month view of Evolution Data Server (EDS) calendars.
  * Add, remove, update events.
  * Quick add (natural language parser) events.
  * Add WebCal, Google calendars.

